title: Added refresh to pass report screen
message:
Added refresh to pass report screen

The MountainPassItemActivity now handles refreshing the data in it's
managed tabs. When the user pressed the refresh button the corresponding
refresh method is called in the displayed fragment and the data is
reloaded.

To achieve this, the report and forecast fragment now only receive the
pass ID and fetch their content from the database.

Pass cameras get the time since 1970 tacked onto the end of the URL to
force the ImageManager to reload the image.

title: Fix for users reporting "Can't install app" error message from Play Store
message:
Fix for users reporting "Can't install app" error message from Play Store

The signature algorithms for jarsigner changed in JDK 7. The default
algorithms have been bumped to SHA-256 and SHA256withRSA respectively,
and are not supported on Android.

Based on this answer from stackoverflow, http://stackoverflow.com/a/9567153
and the Android developer documentation on how to sign your app
manually, http://developer.android.com/tools/publishing/app-signing.html#signing-manually
the additional arguments were added to the mavin-jarsigner-plugin
configuration to override the default signature algorithms.

Closes #20

title: Request permissions at runtime for ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION
message:
Request permissions at runtime for ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION

Beginning in Android 6.0 (API level 23), users grant permissions
to apps while the app is running, not when they install the app.

This commit checks if we access to use the GPS before making the
call to Location Services. There is an issue that if the user
checks "Never ask again" on the permission request dialog the
onConnected method continues to repeatedly hammer calls requesting
permission. Not sure how to code around this.

title: Fix for NullPointerExceptions when viewing a camera image.
message:
Fix for NullPointerExceptions when viewing a camera image.

I believe this was happening when there was an error encountered while trying to

title: Changing menu items at runtime - fix for Android 3.0+
message:
Changing menu items at runtime - fix for Android 3.0+

On Android 2.3.x and lower, the system calls onPrepareOptionsMenu() each
time the user opens the options menu (presses the Menu button).

On Android 3.0 and higher, the options menu is considered to always be open
when menu items are presented in the action bar. When an event occurs and
you want to perform a menu update, you must call invalidateOptionsMenu()
to request that the system call onPrepareOptionsMenu().

http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/menus.html#ChangingTheMenu

single API.

The library will automatically use the native action
bar when appropriate or will automatically wrap a custom
implementation around your layouts. This allows you to easily
develop an application with an action bar for every version of
Android from 2.x and up.

More information: http://actionbarsherlock.com/

title: Fix for IllegalArgumentException: View not attached to window manager
message:
Fix for IllegalArgumentException: View not attached to window manager

My understanding of what was happening when cancelling a ProgressDialog
and the underlying AsyncTask was incorrect in previous code. Changes made
after reviewing the developer docs should fix the problem.

http://developer.android.com/reference/android/os/AsyncTask.html#isCancelled()

Cancelling a task

A task can be cancelled at any time by invoking cancel(boolean). Invoking
this method will cause subsequent calls to isCancelled() to return true.
After invoking this method, onCancelled(Object), instead of onPostExecute(Object)
will be invoked after doInBackground(Object[]) returns. To ensure that a task
is cancelled as quickly as possible, you should always check the return value
of isCancelled() periodically from doInBackground(Object[]),
if possible (inside a loop for instance.)

At Google IO 2010 there was a presentation by Romain Guy and Adam Powell

set the layout_height to "0dp" and layout_weight to "1.0"

title: Fixes to correct app crash during device orientation change
message:
Fixes to correct app crash during device orientation change

Added android:configChanges attribute to <activity> to fix
application crashes if the user changes the phone's orientation
while the progress dialog is not yet dismissed.

Activities in Android are destroyed and recreated on an orientation
change. Because the progress dialog is no longer "attached" to the
view after the activity is re-created, it blows up when an attempt
is made to reference it.

The Canadian Border section displays the northbound border wait times
for the I-5, SR 543, SR 539 and SR 9 routes.

title: Removed duplicate code from traffic map pages
message:
Removed duplicate code from traffic map pages

Turned TrafficMap.java into an abstract class so Seattle, Tacoma
and Olympia traffic maps can subclass it.

title: Add ignored files back into repository
message:
Add ignored files back into repository

EGit will only checkout projects that have been previously setup
in Eclipse. To assist with that I have added the .project file
back into the repository. Also including the .classpath prevents a
bunch of errors as well.
